<subSubSection id="1C8A6552A509892B8F6A4E788A0A333A" lastPageId="24" lastPageNumber="297" pageId="23" pageNumber="296" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="542F36D9A509892B8F6A4E788A7430FA" blockId="23.[794,1399,1865,2082]" lastBlockId="24.[189,794,233,545]" lastPageId="24" lastPageNumber="297" pageId="23" pageNumber="296">
<emphasis id="66E4EACBA50989248F6A4E788B8E367A" bold="true" box="[794,898,1865,1889]" pageId="23" pageNumber="296">Remarks:</emphasis>
The female of 
<taxonomicName id="93904D5AA5098924885A4E7B8CA3367A" authorityName="-" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="WARNCKE" baseAuthorityYear="1992" box="[1066,1199,1866,1889]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Hylaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="296" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="giresunus">
<emphasis id="66E4EACBA5098924885A4E7B8CA3367A" box="[1066,1199,1866,1889]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="296">H. giresunus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus id="8B2B887BA509892488CE4E788D2D367A" box="[1214,1313,1865,1889]" pageId="23" pageNumber="296">holotype</typeStatus>
) differs from 
<taxonomicName id="93904D5AA50989248F104E5B8BDB369A" authorityName="MORAWITZ" authorityYear="1872" box="[864,983,1897,1921]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Prosopis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="23" pageNumber="296" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="glacialis">
<emphasis id="66E4EACBA50989248F104E5B8BDB369A" box="[864,983,1897,1921]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="296">H. glacialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the clypeus almost completely concave throughout its length, while in the latter only the clypeus front edge is transversely impressed. Additionally, in the female the front margin of the clypeus has an arcuate tip. The outline of the head is sub-quadratic (
<taxonomicName id="93904D5AA50989248F53413B8B96393A" authorityName="MORAWITZ" authorityYear="1872" box="[803,922,2057,2081]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Prosopis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="23" pageNumber="296" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="glacialis">
<emphasis id="66E4EACBA50989248F53413B8B96393A" box="[803,922,2057,2081]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="296">H. glacialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: trapezoidal) and the genae are thickened (normal in 
<taxonomicName id="93904D5AA506892B8D4F49DB89BA301A" authorityName="MORAWITZ" authorityYear="1872" box="[319,438,233,257]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Prosopis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="24" pageNumber="297" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="glacialis">
<emphasis id="66E4EACBA506892B8D4F49DB895F301A" box="[319,339,234,257]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="297">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="66E4EACBA506892B8D1049D889BA301A" box="[352,438,233,257]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="297">glacialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The habitus of 
<taxonomicName id="93904D5AA506892B8E0A49DB8AF3301A" authorityName="-" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="WARNCKE" baseAuthorityYear="1992" box="[634,767,234,257]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Hylaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="297" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="giresunus">
<emphasis id="66E4EACBA506892B8E0A49DB8AF3301A" box="[634,767,234,257]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="297">H. giresunus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is much more slender, especially the tergum 1, which is strongly shiny; the sculpture of the propodeum is less pronounced. The males are very similar, also in the terminalia, but the proximal extended apical lobes of sternum 7 may be important. 
<taxonomicName id="93904D5AA506892B8E6048BB8A9930BA" authorityName="-" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="WARNCKE" baseAuthorityYear="1992" box="[528,661,394,417]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Hylaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="297" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="giresunus">
<emphasis id="66E4EACBA506892B8E6048BB8A9930BA" box="[528,661,394,417]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="297">H. giresunus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is certainly a geographical parallel to the European 
<taxonomicName id="93904D5AA506892B8E02489B8AE530DA" authorityName="MORAWITZ" authorityYear="1872" box="[626,745,425,449]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Prosopis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="24" pageNumber="297" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="glacialis">
<emphasis id="66E4EACBA506892B8E02489B8AE530DA" box="[626,745,425,449]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="297">H. glacialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the female appears to be discrete from it.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="542F36D9A506892B8CCD48DB8A0A333A" blockId="24.[189,794,233,545]" pageId="24" pageNumber="297">
<taxonomicName id="93904D5AA506892B8CCD48DB8933331A" authorityName="-" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="WARNCKE" baseAuthorityYear="1992" box="[189,319,490,513]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Hylaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="297" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="giresunus">
<emphasis id="66E4EACBA506892B8CCD48DB8933331A" box="[189,319,490,513]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="297">H. giresunus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a montane (at 
<quantity id="93689B3CA506892B8E6848D88AA6331A" box="[536,682,489,513]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.05" metricValueMax="2.4" metricValueMin="1.7" pageId="24" pageNumber="297" unit="m" value="2050.0" valueMax="2400.0" valueMin="1700.0">1700–2400 m</quantity>
), sparsely recorded species (3 provinces).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
